{
    "analysis": "The Executor computed global P95/P05 per (cmdb_id,kpi_name) for metric.csv and found the top-20 anomaly candidates are all adservice KPIs. However, those KPIs are constant across their full series so P95==P05 and every point in the incident window is flagged — a threshold artifact rather than a true anomaly. error_logs.csv shows repeated frontend warnings (e.g., 'failed to retrieve...') at the window start (21:30). Given metric thresholds are unreliable for adservice (constant metrics), we should now move to trace analysis to identify downstream faulty services/pods in transaction paths originating from frontend, and to find the earliest trace-level anomalies that coincide with frontend error logs.",
