{
    "analysis": "We have completed metric and trace threshold scans and found they are unreliable here because many KPI/trace series are constant (P95==P05 or P95==0), producing threshold artifacts. error_logs.csv shows concentrated warning messages on frontend pods (frontend-2, frontend-0, frontend-1) starting at the incident window start (earliest frontend-2 at 2022-03-20T21:30:00+08:00). This suggests the failure surface is observed first in frontend pods. To localize the root cause we must identify which downstream service(s) the frontends called that failed or became slow/empty. Trace telemetry contains per-pod incoming-from-frontend metrics (trace.from_frontend-*.{row_count,duration_mean,duration_p95,error_rate}) which can indicate downstream impacts (e.g., row_count drop, error_rate increase, latency spike). Since global P95/P05 collapsed, we'll use global medians as a robust baseline and compare medians inside the incident window to the global medians to find the largest relative deviations for trace series originating from frontend. The result will highlight which downstream pod(s)/services experienced the biggest functional change coincident with frontend warnings.",
